        {
            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "> should `vim.pack` treat `1` / `v1` / `1.0` / `v1.0` as semver tags?\n\nI think this has some merit but does it benefit the long-term plugin ecosystem? If we want more people to use vim.pack and follow a semver-like syntax we probably shouldn't loosen the rules. If we treat our current strict semver protocol as being the correct pattern should we not encourage plugin authors to align to it? Over time this problem should lessen as developers adopt the strict pattern.\n\n>Or is it more important to align with what vim.version.parse(x, { strict = true }) says a semver is?\n\nShould we consider defaulting strict to true and treating it as the standard? Considering git is our registry for now would it make sense to follow the other package managers and maintain a clear syntax?\n\nThe fallback for non compliant plugins could be just setting strict to false. ",
